<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="762" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2780: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-26T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 26,
                                        1922—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>156. Your 203, October 24, 10 p.m.</p>
                        <p>You will advise Foreign Office as indicated in Department’s No. 147, via
                                Paris,<note n="11" xml:id="d762fn11">See telegram no. 311, Oct. 13,
                                to the Ambassador in France, <ref target="#pg_920">p.
                                920</ref>.</note> omitting references in text to Italy’s failure to
                            reply and adding that the Governments of Japan and France have already
                            expressed their concurrence in this Government’s proposal to wind up
                            Inter-Allied Technical Board on October 31.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>